2026-04-16 12:14:12 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module 6 output (+) cable/connection', 'Control module 6 internal switch path'] hypothesis_explanation='The voltage survey shows that up to the input of control module 6 the series path is healthy: PSU and modules 1–5 have ~12 V on their (+) conductors and 0 V on their (−) conductors, and control module 6 input (+) is also at 11.99 V. However, control module 6 output (+) is at 0 V, and so are all conductors in modules 7–8 and the load input. This means the series 12 V line is interrupted inside or immediately after control module 6, not by polarity inversion.\n\nBecause the measurement notes that the input “n” port of module 6 is reported as disconnected, and there is no 12 V on its output side when the switch is ON, the most likely root cause is an open circuit in control module 6: either the internal switch / PCB trace that should connect input (+) to output (+) when ON is open, or the output (+) cable/terminal is not actually bonded to the internal circuit. Replacing/repairing control module 6 (or its output (+) connector) should restore continuity to modules 7–8 and the load, allowing the lamp to operate when all switches are on.'
